# tRPC Conventions

- Keep procedures typed with Zod input schemas and clear return shapes.
- Use tRPC for internal app APIs; keep Shopify webhook/proxy as plain route endpoints.
- Build context from trusted request data (`shop`, `customerId`) provided by verified boundaries.
- Procedures orchestrate services; repositories own all DB access.
- Prefer incremental migration: route -> caller -> procedure -> service.
